      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While increasing hydration is a good idea, relying solely on water and supplements may not address underlying issues. Supplementing with vitamin C might help alleviate some symptoms, but it's not a substitute for medical guidance. Consider discussing your concerns and monitoring your symptoms with your doctor, so they can help determine the best course of action. If you're genuinely concerned, your doctor may recommend a subtle adjustment to your medication or a follow-up appointment rather than an immediate visit.",
      "source": "target",
